            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EJoy%20is%20the%20biggest%20prize%20Satan%20could%20ever%20steal%20from%20a%20Christian.%20Someone%20once%20said%2C%20%22If%20he%20can%20steal%20your%20joy%2C%20he%20can%20spoil%20your%20goods.%22%20The%20prophet%20Habakkuk%20knew%20how%20important%20it%20was%20to%20keep%20his%20joy%2C%20and%20he%20was%20determined%20to%20hold%20on%20to%20it%20tightly%2C%20even%20in%20the%20most%20difficult%20of%20circumstances.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EJoy%20is%20the%20one%20precious%20commodity%20Satan%20cannot%20take%20from%20you%20unless%20you%20give%20it%20to%20him.%20When%20you%20have%20your%20joy%2C%20you%20will%20say%20with%20Habakkuk%2C%20%22The%20Sovereign%20Lord%20is%20my%20strength!%20He%20will%20make%20me%20as%20sure-footed%20as%20a%20deer%20and%20bring%20me%20safely%20over%20the%20mountains%22%20(Habakkuk%203%3A19).%20The%20little%20deer's%20feet%20are%20so%20nimble%20that%20even%20when%20he%20is%20knocked%20from%20a%20towering%20precipice%2C%20he%20still%20lands%20on%20his%20feet.%20With%20joy%20in%20your%20heart%2C%20you%20will%20always%20land%20on%20your%20feet%2C%20no%20matter%20the%20trial.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EPerhaps%20you%20can%20rejoice%20when%20everything%20is%20going%20perfectly%2C%20but%20what%20about%20when%20the%20bank%20balance%20is%20zero%20and%20all%20your%20efforts%20seem%20to%20be%20unfruitful%3F%20Purpose%20today%20to%20%22always%20be%20joyful.%20Keep%20on%20praying.%20No%20matter%20what%20happens%2C%20always%20be%20thankful%2C%20for%20this%20is%20God's%20will%20for%20you%20who%20belong%20to%20Christ%20Jesus%22%20(1%20Thessalonians%205%3A16).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ERejoice!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
